{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RCAHyMA2afDxMDCVSbFvBu","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: \"PRD-227.4\"\n3\ttitle: \"Migrate the extraction workflow to use a template\"\n4\tkind: task\n5\tstatus: ready\n6\tpriority: medium\n7\teffort: xs\n8\tcapability: simple\n9\tparent: \"[[PRD-227-workflow-templates]]\"\n10\tdepends_on:\n11\t  - \"[[PRD-227.2-prd-implementation-template]]\"\n12\tblocks: []\n13\timpacts:\n14\t  - workflows/extraction/workflow.py\n15\tworkflow: null\n16\ttarget_version: null\n17\tcreated: 2026-04-08\n18\tupdated: 2026-04-08\n19\ttags:\n20\t  - harness\n21\t  - workflow\n22\t---\n23\t\n24\t# Migrate the extraction workflow to use a template\n25\t\n26\t## Summary\n27\t\n28\tMigrate `workflows/extraction/workflow.py` to use `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE.compose(...)`, verifying that the template works for non-default workflows. If the extraction workflow's open/close tasks differ enough from the standard template, define a variant template and document why. This task surfaces template flexibility questions early.\n29\t\n30\t## Requirements\n31\t\n32\t1. Analyze the extraction workflow's current task list to determine if it matches the `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE`'s open/close sequence.\n33\t2. If it matches: refactor to use `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE.compose(...)` with the extraction-specific middle.\n34\t3. If it does not match: either define a new template (e.g. `EXTRACTION_TEMPLATE`) or document why the extraction workflow cannot use the standard template and what invariants it needs instead.\n35\t4. Document the decision in a code comment or the workflow file itself.\n36\t\n37\t## Technical Approach\n38\t\n39\t### Step 1: Compare task lists\n40\t\n41\tRead the current `workflows/extraction/workflow.py` and compare its opening and closing builtins against `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE.open` and `.close`.\n42\t\n43\t### Step 2: Migrate or document\n44\t\n45\tIf the open/close match:\n46\t```python\n47\tfrom darkfactory.templates_builtin import PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE\n48\t\n49\tworkflow = PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE.compose(\n50\t    name=\"extraction\",\n51\t    description=\"Workflow for extraction-type PRD tasks.\",\n52\t    applies_to=lambda prd, prds: ...,\n53\t    priority=...,\n54\t    middle=[...extraction-specific tasks...],\n55\t)\n56\t```\n57\t\n58\tIf they don't match, create a new template in `templates_builtin.py` or a local template, and document the differences.\n59\t\n60\t## Acceptance Criteria\n61\t\n62\t- [ ] AC-1: The extraction workflow either uses `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE` or its own template — it is not a flat `Workflow(tasks=[...])` anymore.\n63\t- [ ] AC-2: If a new template was needed, it is defined and documented with rationale.\n64\t- [ ] AC-3: All existing tests for the extraction workflow pass.\n65\t- [ ] AC-4: The decision (same template vs different template) is documented in code or comments.\n66\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d010088e-6429-4c1e-aa66-519315c26c5c","uuid":"411a7376-8106-43e7-a26e-c0609e888803","timestamp":"2026-04-09T04:33:33.677Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.darkfactory/prds/PRD-227.4-migrate-extraction-workflow.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-227.4\"\ntitle: \"Migrate the extraction workflow to use a template\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: medium\neffort: xs\ncapability: simple\nparent: \"[[PRD-227-workflow-templates]]\"\ndepends_on:\n  - \"[[PRD-227.2-prd-implementation-template]]\"\nblocks: []\nimpacts:\n  - workflows/extraction/workflow.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - harness\n  - workflow\n---\n\n# Migrate the extraction workflow to use a template\n\n## Summary\n\nMigrate `workflows/extraction/workflow.py` to use `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE.compose(...)`, verifying that the template works for non-default workflows. If the extraction workflow's open/close tasks differ enough from the standard template, define a variant template and document why. This task surfaces template flexibility questions early.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Analyze the extraction workflow's current task list to determine if it matches the `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE`'s open/close sequence.\n2. If it matches: refactor to use `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE.compose(...)` with the extraction-specific middle.\n3. If it does not match: either define a new template (e.g. `EXTRACTION_TEMPLATE`) or document why the extraction workflow cannot use the standard template and what invariants it needs instead.\n4. Document the decision in a code comment or the workflow file itself.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### Step 1: Compare task lists\n\nRead the current `workflows/extraction/workflow.py` and compare its opening and closing builtins against `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE.open` and `.close`.\n\n### Step 2: Migrate or document\n\nIf the open/close match:\n```python\nfrom darkfactory.templates_builtin import PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE\n\nworkflow = PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE.compose(\n    name=\"extraction\",\n    description=\"Workflow for extraction-type PRD tasks.\",\n    applies_to=lambda prd, prds: ...,\n    priority=...,\n    middle=[...extraction-specific tasks...],\n)\n```\n\nIf they don't match, create a new template in `templates_builtin.py` or a local template, and document the differences.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: The extraction workflow either uses `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE` or its own template — it is not a flat `Workflow(tasks=[...])` anymore.\n- [ ] AC-2: If a new template was needed, it is defined and documented with rationale.\n- [ ] AC-3: All existing tests for the extraction workflow pass.\n- [ ] AC-4: The decision (same template vs different template) is documented in code or comments.\n","numLines":66,"startLine":1,"totalLines":66}}}
